{"word":"εὐεργός","slug":"εὐεργός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐεργός</b></el> <el>(εὐ-εργός, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>Ἔργω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>doing good</i> or <i>well, upright</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>well-wrought, well-tilled</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>easy to work</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}